{"word":"ὀργυιά","slug":"ὀργυιά","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ὀργυιά</el></b> <b>(<el>ὄργυια</el>), <el>ᾶς, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὀρέγω\">ὀρέγω</a></el> ‘reach, stretch (out)’; the form <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὀργυιά\">ὀργυιά</a></el> is late] of arms outstretched about 1.8 meters, a nautical term for measuring depth, <b>fathom <a href='B:510 27:28'>Ac 27:28</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ὀργίλος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ὀρέγω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}